        <section id="intro-section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>The Health Monitoring System is designed to revolutionize health management on campus by addressing the challenges faced by traditional health monitoring methods:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Manual record-keeping: The system automates data collection and management, reducing the need for manual record-keeping.</li>
                <li>Limited accessibility to medical resources: By integrating with electronic health records (EHR) systems and offering telemedicine capabilities, the system improves access to medical resources.</li>
                <li>Fragmented data management: The system provides seamless data sharing and analysis through integration with EHR systems, ensuring centralized and comprehensive data management.</li>
                <li><strong>Key features of the system:</strong></li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Real-time health data collection through wearable devices or mobile apps.</li>
                    <li>Integration with electronic health records (EHR) systems for seamless data sharing and analysis.</li>
                    <li>Personalized health recommendations based on individual health profiles.</li>
                    <li>Telemedicine capabilities for remote consultations and follow-ups.</li>
                    <li>Automated alerts for critical health events.</li>
                    <li>Privacy safeguards compliant with healthcare regulations.</li>
                </ul>
            </ul>
